					<a href="mailto:?subject=Check%20out%20%22The%20Brainpickings%20brouhaha%20and%20the%20problem%20with%20affiliate%20links%22&#038;body=Interesting%20comment%20on%20%22The%20Brainpickings%20brouhaha%20and%20the%20problem%20with%20affiliate%20links%22%20by%20bob%3Ahttp%3A%2F%2Fpaidcontent.org%2F2013%2F02%2F14%2Fthe-brainpickings-brouhaha-and-the-problem-with-affiliate-links%2F%23comment-199974" title="Share via Email" class="goicon icon-email"></a>
				</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
							</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		<ol class='children'>
		<li class="comment odd alt depth-2 comment clearfix li-comment highlander-comment" id="comment-200028" data-comment-id="200028">
			<div class="div-comment" id="div-comment-200028">
				<div class="comment-meta clearfix">
					<div class="comment-author-avatar">
						<!-- avatar info cached Fri, 15 Feb 13 17:32:10 +0000 --><a class="avatar-placeholder" rel="nofollow" href="http://www.gravatar.com/avatar/d41d8cd98f00b204e9800998ecf8427e?d=http://pro.gigaom.com/wp-content/plugins/buddypress/bp-core/images/mystery-man.jpg&amp;s=50&amp;r=G"></a>					</div>
					<div class="comment-info">
						<cite>Carissa</cite>
						<a href="http://paidcontent.org/2013/02/14/the-brainpickings-brouhaha-and-the-problem-with-affiliate-links/#comment-200028" class="comment-permalink">Friday, February 15 2013</a>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="comment-content">
					<div class="comment-text">
						<p>Sponsored links and affiliate links are different things. Sponsored links are something you&#8217;re paid to put on your site. Affiliate links are something you create linking to a product, and if the reader decides to buy it, then you get a small kickback. Amazon doesn&#8217;t tell her what affiliate links to use, with a sponsored link they would. Huge difference.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="comment-sharing clearfix">
						<span class="comment-sharing-inner comment-sharing-reply">
